Spermatids in the seminiferous ducts of testis displayed distinct staining in potential acrocomes. Remaining normal tissues were generally negative.
Malignant cells were generally negative. A few cases of colorectal cancers and embryonal carcinoma of testis exhibited moderate luminal membranous staining.
